wikipedia_page.main: James Nathaniel Cunliffe (5 July 1912  – 21 November 1986) was an English footballer who played as an inside forward.

response: * November (undated) – Jimmy Cunliffe, 74, scored 73 goals in 1974 league games for Everton in the six seasons preceding the outbreak of World War II, and was capped once for England.
*Jimmy Cunliffe (born 1912), English footballer who played as an inside forward
His cousin was Jimmy Cunliffe, also a footballer.
